# Conclusion

Searching algorithms are fundamental techniques used to locate data efficiently.
Different algorithms are suitable for different types of datasets and applications.

* Linear Search is simple but slower.
* Binary Search is highly efficient for sorted data.
* Jump and Interpolation searches improve searching under specific conditions.
* Exponential Search works well for large or infinite arrays.
* Ternary Search is useful in optimization and mathematical problems.
